Description: You get the information whether the country spends between 4% and 6% of its GDP on education (YES) or less/more than that (NO). 4% - 6% is a rather average value, neither especially little nor very much.
You get the information whether the country has a high electricity consumption per person (more than 4200kWh per person) (YES) or less than that (NO).
You get the information whether the country has a low electricity consumption per person (less than 1300kWh per person) (YES) or more than that (NO).
You get the information whether the country has a high total electricity consumption (more than 56 billion kWh) (YES) or less than that (NO).
You get the information whether the country has a low total electricity consumption (less than 8 billion kWh) (YES) or more than that (NO).
You get the information whether the country has high total exports (more than $77 billion) (YES) or less than that (NO).
You get the information whether the country has low exports (less than $10 billion) (YES) or more than that (NO).
You get the information whether the country has an inflation rate between 2% and 4% of GDP (YES) or less/more than that (NO). This is a rather average value, neither especially little nor very much.
You get the information whether the country has a low number of Internet users (less than 1,168,000) (YES) or more than that (NO).
You get the information whether the country has high public debt (more than 62% of GDP) (YES) or less than that (NO).
You get the information whether the country belongs to Asia (YES) or to another region (NO).
You get the information whether the country belongs to the Sub Saharan Africa region, that is all countries south of the Sarah desert (YES) or to another region (NO).
You get the information whether the country has a low unemployment rate (less than 6%) (YES) or more than that (NO).
